---

@type NodePool
@kind struct
@purpose Flat array storage for all AST nodes. Avoids heap-allocated tree structures. Nodes reference children by integer index into this pool. The pool is append-only during parsing.
@fields
  nodes: [Expr] — Flat array of all AST nodes; index 0 is always a sentinel
@invariants
  - Index 0 is always an EkNone sentinel created by new_pool()
  - Nodes are never removed or reordered after creation
  - pool_size() returns len(nodes), so valid indices are 0..pool_size()-1
@source_file src/parser/ast.aria
