---

@type DeclInfo
@kind struct
@purpose Metadata about a single top-level declaration. Records token ranges for the declaration body so the resolver/checker can parse individual declarations on demand without re-parsing the entire file.
@fields
  kind: DeclKind — Declaration type
  name: str — Declaration name (empty for entry blocks; prefixed for special forms like "_bench:", "_extern", "_alias:", "_fixture:")
  token_start: i64 — Token index where declaration starts (at the keyword)
  body_start: i64 — Token index where body starts (at = or {)
  body_end: i64 — Token index where body ends (one past the closing brace or expression end)
  is_pub: bool — Whether declaration is public (preceded by pub keyword)
  node_idx: i64 — Index into NodePool for the parsed AST node; 0 until _bridge_ast_to_decl_index populates it
@source_file src/parser/ast.aria
@source_line 376

---

@type DeclIndex
@kind struct
@purpose Registry of all top-level declarations in a source file. Enables the resolver and checker to look up declarations by name and kind without walking the full AST. Built by build_decl_index via a fast token scan, then enriched with node_idx values by bridging against the full parse.
@fields
  decls: [DeclInfo] — All top-level declarations; index 0 is a sentinel
@invariants
  - Index 0 is always a DkNone sentinel
  - Declarations are stored in source order
  - After build_decl_index completes, every non-sentinel entry has node_idx populated (pointing into the companion NodePool)
@source_file src/parser/ast.aria
