---

@type Parser
@kind struct
@purpose Immutable parser state threaded through all parse functions. Every mutation (advancing position, adding a node, recording an error) returns a new Parser value. This functional style is required because the bootstrap compiler does not support mutable struct fields.
@fields
  tokens: [Token] — Token stream from lexer
  pos: i64 — Current token position
  pool: NodePool — AST node accumulator
  diagnostics: DiagnosticBag — Parse diagnostics
@invariants
  - pos is always in range [0, tokens.len()]
  - pool grows monotonically — nodes are never removed
@effects Allocates new Parser/NodePool values on every mutation (append-heavy)
@source_file src/parser/parser.aria
@source_line 8

---

@type PR
@kind struct
@purpose Parse result pair returned by every internal parse function. Bundles the updated parser state with the expression node that was just parsed. This is the universal return type for the recursive descent functions.
@fields
  p: Parser — Updated parser state (advanced position, possibly new nodes in pool, possibly new diagnostics)
  e: Expr — Parsed expression result (not yet added to pool — caller decides where to place it)
@notes The returned Expr in PR.e is NOT yet in the pool. The caller must explicitly call _padd() to add it. This separation allows the caller to control the pool index where the node lands, which is critical for the child list indirection pattern.
@source_file src/parser/parser.aria
