---

# mk_* Constructor Functions
#
# These are pure factory functions that construct Expr nodes with the correct ExprKind
# and field encoding for each AST node type. They exist to provide a documented API for
# the Expr struct's overloaded fields (s1/s2/b1/b2/c0/c1/c2/list_start/list_count).
#
# All mk_* functions:
# - Are pure (no side effects, no pool mutation)
# - Return an Expr that is NOT yet in the pool — the caller adds it via _padd/pool_add
# - Initialize unused fields to zero values ("", false, 0)
# - Take a Span for source location tracking
#
# The parser itself often constructs Expr literals directly (bypassing mk_*) when it
# needs to set c0/c1/c2/list_start/list_count to specific pool indices. The mk_*
# functions primarily document the field encoding contract.

---

